  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Does Cyanogen 13.1 on Moto G3 support VOLTE? If yes, how can I turn on?",
  "response": "Cyanogen 13.1, based on Android 6.0.1 Marshmallow, does have the capability to support VoLTE (Voice over LTE) depending on the device and the carrier. However, the Moto G3's support for VoLTE on Cyanogen 13.1 can be a bit tricky and may not be officially supported due to several factors:\n\n1. **Device Hardware and Firmware**: The Moto G3 must have the necessary hardware and firmware to support VoLTE. Not all variants of the Moto G3 may support VoLTE.\n\n2. **Carrier Support**: VoLTE needs to be supported and enabled by your carrier. Even if your device supports VoLTE, it won't work if your carrier doesn't support it.\n\n3. **ROM Support**: The Cyanogen 13.1 ROM for Moto G3 may not have VoLTE enabled by default. Some custom ROMs enable VoLTE, but it depends on the developers and the specific build.\n\nAssuming that your Moto G3 variant and your carrier support VoLTE, here are the steps to enable it if Cyanogen 13.1 supports it:\n\n1. **Check for VoLTE Settings**: Go to `Settings` > `Wireless & networks` > `Mobile networks`. Look for an option labeled `VoLTE` or `Enhanced 4G LTE Mode`. If you see this option, enable it.\n\n2. **Dialer Codes**: Sometimes, you can enable VoLTE using dialer codes. Try entering `*#*#86583#*#*` or `*#*#4636#*#*` in the Phone app. This will open a hidden menu where you might find options to enable VoLTE. Navigate through the menus and look for VoLTE settings.\n\n3. **APN Settings**: Ensure your APN settings are correctly configured. Incorrect APN settings can prevent VoLTE from working. You can find these under `Settings` > `Wireless & networks` > `Mobile networks` > `Access Point Names`.\n\n4. **Update the ROM**: If VoLTE is not available, check for updates to your ROM. Developers may add VoLTE support in newer builds.\n\n5. **Check with the ROM Developer**: Visit the XDA Developers forum or the specific thread where you downloaded the Cyanogen 13.1 ROM for Moto G3. Developers often provide information on supported features and troubleshooting steps.\n\nIf you follow these steps and still can't get VoLTE to work, it's likely that the Cyanogen 13.1 ROM for your Moto G3 does not support it, or your carrier does not support VoLTE on this device.",
